description:
File: rust/lichen-kiss/src/bridge.rs
Line: 185-187

The `set_epoch` method allows setting any epoch value (0-255) with no validation:

```rust
pub fn set_epoch(&mut self, epoch: u8) {
    self.default_epoch = epoch;
}
```

Impact: Unlike `with_epoch` which has at least a debug_assert, this method has NO validation. A caller could set epoch to any value including 0-127, violating spec section 4.4 requirements for replay protection.

Fix: Add validation (at minimum matching `with_epoch`'s debug_assert, but preferably a proper assert or Result return)
